        <h2 class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-[#FAFF00]">HOW WE EVALUATE BONUS VALUE</h2>

        <p class="text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Headline numbers are misleading. A "400% up to $40,000" bonus sounds incredible until you check the 60x wagering requirement. Our rating system looks past the marketing to assess what a bonus is actually worth to a real player.
        </p>

        <p class="text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">Wagering requirement weight:</span> This is the single biggest factor. We calculate the expected cost of clearing each bonus using average house edges. Lower wagering means higher real value.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">Time limit fairness:</span> A 30x requirement with 30 days is reasonable. The same requirement with 7 days forces rushed, reckless play. We penalize unrealistic deadlines.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">Game restriction analysis:</span> If only low-RTP slots count toward wagering, the real cost of clearing increases. We factor in which games contribute and at what weight.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">Withdrawal cap impact:</span> A $100 no-deposit bonus with a $50 withdrawal cap means you can never realize the full bonus value. We adjust our ratings to reflect maximum achievable value.
